    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: 
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "As you\u2019ve heard a few times up to this point, when
          you\u2019re in Play mode, none of the changes you make are saved. Make
          sure to pay attention when entering and exiting Play mode so that you don't
          lose your changes! \n\nBy default, the <b>Editor</b> windows around the
          <b>Game</b> view become a tiny bit darker when you enter Play mode to help
          visually distinguish between Play mode and Edit mode \u2014 this is known
          as the <b>Play mode tint.</b> \n\nIn this step, you\u2019ll edit the <b>Play</b>
          mode tint to make it more noticeable so that you\u2019ll always realize
          when you\u2019re in Play mode and avoid losing unsaved changes."
