    - m_Type: 1
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Instructions
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "<b>1.</b>  From the main menu, select <b>Edit</b> > <b>Preferences</b>
          (macOS: <b>Unity</b> > <b>Settings</b>). \n\n<b>2.</b>  In the left menu,
          select <b>Colors,</b> then change the <b>Playmode tint</b> color to have
          a subtle color instead of gray. \n\n<b>3.</b>  Enter <b>Play</b> mode to
          test the new tint. \n\nThe color should be very noticeable, but still allow
          you to read text in the <b>Editor</b> windows.\n\n<b>4.</b>  If the color
          needs further adjustment, return to the preferences menu and edit it."
